messages.message: Who owns the Granafa data? It would be helpful to get clarity on this asap as this data is very valuable in managing the customer engagements
these queries are from licenses table, so @mfichman would know more on the correctness of the data and query

Hey @Andrew Sherrill @Tom -- we are a bit behind in this area. The metrics for Commercial users comes from a different source, since these users use Metronome rather than LicenseService. tl;dr, the data is stored in opensearch rather than the license_metrics table in the DB.

@Gauti owns the dashboard, but I helped him with the consumption part. I'll provide a quick link to Grafana that should unblock you, and then chat with him separately about adding it to the official consumption dashboard.
Thanks! THis is not an urgent block. We had just got used to using Grafana to keep an eye on how our customers were using AI Hub :slightly_smiling_face:
You should still be able to see app run metrics though! The only thing that wouldn't work for commercial is the units consumption dashboard.
